  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "Ah, the quest for the most romantic movies is a delightful one!  Romance is subjective, so what one person finds swoon-worthy, another might find cheesy.  However, based on popularity, critical acclaim, and cultural impact, here's a list of some of the most consistently cited and beloved romantic movies, broken down by category:\n\n**Timeless Classics (Golden Age of Hollywood):**\n\n*   **Casablanca (1942):**  Sacrifice, longing, and timeless dialogue make this a perennial favorite.\n*   **Gone With the Wind (1939):** A sweeping epic of love and loss against the backdrop of the Civil War.\n*   **Roman Holiday (1953):**  Innocence, charm, and a forbidden romance between a princess and a journalist in Rome.\n\n**Classic Dramas:**\n\n*   **Doctor Zhivago (1965):** Epic and tragic, a love story set against the backdrop of the Russian Revolution.\n*   **Love Story (1970):**  The quintessential tearjerker about young love and devastating loss.\n*   **The Way We Were (1973):**  Barbra Streisand and Robert Redford star in this story of two people with fundamentally different values who are drawn together and then torn apart.\n\n**Modern Classics (Late 20th Century):**\n\n*   **When Harry Met Sally... (1989):**  A witty and insightful exploration of whether men and women can truly be just friends.\n*   **Ghost (1990):**  Love transcends even death in this supernatural romance.\n*   **The Princess Bride (1987):** A beloved fairy tale with adventure, humor, and undeniable romance.\n\n**Romantic Dramas (More Recent):**\n\n*   **The Notebook (2004):**  A passionate and enduring love story that spans decades.\n*   **Atonement (2007):**  A beautiful but heartbreaking tale of love, guilt, and redemption.\n*   **Call Me By Your Name (2017):** A coming-of-age story set in Italy, exploring first love and self-discovery.\n*   **Titanic (1997):**  A grand love story set against the backdrop of a historical tragedy.\n\n**Romantic Comedies:**\n\n*   **Annie Hall (1977):** Quirky, insightful, and considered a groundbreaking rom-com.\n*   **Pretty Woman (1990):**  A modern Cinderella story with plenty of charm.\n*   **Sleepless in Seattle (1993):**  Fate, destiny, and a cross-country connection.\n*   **You've Got Mail (1998):**  A charming story about finding love in the digital age.\n*   **10 Things I Hate About You (1999):** A modern adaptation of \"The Taming of the Shrew\" with a great soundtrack and cast.\n*   **Love Actually (2003):**  An ensemble cast explores the many facets of love during the Christmas season.\n*   **500 Days of Summer (2009):**  A deconstruction of the typical rom-com narrative.\n*   **Crazy Rich Asians (2018):**  A visually stunning and culturally rich romantic comedy.\n*   **Palm Springs (2020):** Combines rom-com with time loop.\n\n**Indie/Art House Romance:**\n\n*   **Amelie (2001):**  A whimsical and charming French film about a young woman who finds joy in helping others.\n*   **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004):** A unique and mind-bending exploration of love, memory, and heartbreak.\n*   **Lost in Translation (2003):**  A poignant and melancholic story of connection in a foreign land.\n*   **Like Water for Chocolate (1992):** Magical realism and passionate love combine in this Mexican film.\n*   **In the Mood for Love (2000):** Elegant and atmospheric, a story of unspoken longing in 1960s Hong Kong.\n\n**LGBTQ+ Romance:**\n\n*   **Brokeback Mountain (2005):**  A groundbreaking and heartbreaking story of forbidden love.\n*   **Carol (2015):**  A beautifully shot and acted period piece about a forbidden romance between two women.\n*   **Moonlight (2016):**  A coming-of-age story with a poignant and subtle romantic subplot.\n*  **Portrait of a Lady on Fire (2019):** A mesmerizing and intimate historical romance.\n*   **Love, Simon (2018):** A sweet and relatable coming-of-age story about a gay teenager.\n\n**Things to consider when choosing:**\n\n*   **Your personal preferences:**  Do you prefer grand epics, quirky comedies, or tear-jerking dramas?\n*   **Your mood:**  Are you looking for something light and fluffy or something more intense and thought-provoking?\n*   **The company you're keeping:**  What does your partner/friend enjoy?\n\nNo matter what you choose, I hope you find a movie that warms your heart! Enjoy!\n",
